rComments: Best. Professor. EVER! This guy is legitimately so cool. Like I can't even describe you have to take his course to understand what I mean. Most friendly guy ever. Really helpful too!

Took both eco302,and eco321 with him. Great experience, knowledgeable professor and very  patient with all kinds of questions from the class. Strongly recommend attending all the lectures,which will save a lot time to read through the textbooks.
very clever gentleman...best eco prof ever
attend his lectures. he is wisest prof..ever..:)  love him
i recommend taking eco321 with professor rotstein. the tests are pretty straighforward, especially if you go to lecture because he will drill the material into you through repitition.

If you want to take ECO321, take it during summer, coz this prof will be teaching through out the whole course! Definitely take ECO302! Yes, there will be participation marks, a 50% research paper and a book review.  But almost everyone got A! Definitely talk to the prof if you have any problems.  I even asked him how to write a research paper~lol

When I first walked into his class, I couldn't believe it.  The typical image of a professor popped into mind being an old man speeching in a half-dead manner.  Turns out he's actually a great prof and intelligent man.  Although repetitive, he's knowledgeable and helpful.

Rotstein's lectures, while incisive, are incredibly repetitive. Like a lot of people as old as sin, he has about 5-6 basic points which he will repeat in every lecture. The reading material is interesting (and pretty useful), however, as are the in-class debates and the indisciplinary makeup of the student. This class should be a 4th year seminar.
He is definetly a great professor and a very friendly person. His lectures are presented in a calm, collective and organized manner. I always enjoyed going to his class.
One of the best profs I have encountered.  Easy going and is passionate about what he teaches.
Wonderful man, truly I can say I have walked away from his class and ACTUALLY have learned somethind...now that is rare at UofT!
